   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE ALL-INCLUSIVE CHRIST REALIZED IN HIS SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The all-inclusive Christ is realized in His Spirit Rom 8:9 .</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The Spirit, as the realization of the all-inclusive Christ, consisting of the unsearchable riches of Christ Eph 3:8 with the bountiful supply for the believers life and work Phil 1:19 , indwells the believers spirits Rom 8:11, 16 .</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>This is the processed Triune God becoming one with His enjoyers.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>When we experience the all-inclusive Christ as the Spirit and speak Him in the meeting, that meeting is according to God s economy in His fatherhood.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>THE SPIRIT EMBODIED</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>IN THE LIVING WORD OF CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Triune God is embodied in Christ, Christ is realized in and as the Spirit, and the Spirit is embodied in the living word of Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The processed Triune God, the all-inclusive Christ, and the Spirit are invisible, but the Word is visible and can be pray-read by us.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>When we pray-read the Word, we are pray-reading the processed Triune God, we are pray-reading Christ, and we are pray-reading the all-inclusive, bountiful, life-giving Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Our God is pray-readable, Christ is pray-readable, and the all-inclusive, bountiful, life-giving Spirit is pray-readable.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The Word is composed of the bountiful supply of Christ s all-inclusive Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The living word is also available in our mouth and even in our heart Rom 10:6-10 .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The word talked about in Romans 10 is not the word in letter.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>This word is living, and it must be the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Otherwise, how could the word be in our mouth and also in our heart?</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Sometimes we may not need a Bible to enjoy the living word because we can pray-read some verses we have memorized.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>This is why it is good to keep some verses in our memory.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>When we pray-read the printed Word, the word gets in our mouth and in our heart.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>At that time, the word becomes the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>THE WAY TO PARTAKE OF AND ENJOY</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>THE RICHES OF CHRIST</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The way to partake of and enjoy the riches of Christ is to confess with our mouth, Lord Jesus Rom 10:9-10 , calling upon the name of the Lord vv.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>12-13 , and to pray-read His Word.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The very Christ today is available in His name and in His Word.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>We can call on His name in any place, on any occasion, and at any time.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>His name is so available, and this name simply denotes Himself, His very Person.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Moreover, all the content of this Person is condensed and embodied in the written Word.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>We have a name and a book.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>We can call on His name at any time, and we can pray-read the Word all the time.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>When we call on His name, we get Him.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>When we pray-read His Word, we enjoy Him.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>We have to practice calling on His name and pray-reading His Word daily at all times.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>When we pray-read the Word, we are actually pray-reading the processed Triune God with all His unsearchable riches.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>Hallelujah for the availability of Christ!</S>
   </TEXT>
